In November 07, it appeared that I have “won” the battle when I woke up, but my conditions were not good at all; I had amnesia, I was paralyzed and mute. Which is when I realized that I just won a battle but the war was still on… The very first moment that I became aware of what I have been through, I decided that I needed to work as hard as I could, in order to comeback and regain control of my life. Which ultimately was a humongous task because, as it was expected, after spending almost a year in medical leave I was unemployed and with very little promises for the future, due to my condition. The process was hard, it was just like going back in time and suddenly becoming a baby; I had to re learn every little thing everyone takes granted: from talking to walking, reading to speaking, etc. My condition forced me to live a stress-free life -Doctors’ orders- which was easier said than done when you are trying to bounce back from the afterlife, then the internet played its magic… A kind of new and mysterious platform called Facebook became the center of my daily life, there I was reintroduced to my friends, started talking to them, and suddenly, while I was in my bed, I begun to feel Like I was living their adventures, thru their posts. After a couple of months I was even able to make a living out of Facebook by becoming some sort of Expert in that new puzzling tool, that no marketer new much about, just because I had to spend so much time in it… Time passed by and here I am, still fighting with the disease …I became a full time entrepreneur and a very passionate professional… Life has given me a second chance and I plan on getting the most out of it.
